INSTALL iTAK 

Download iTAK from the Apple App  store. Use the provided QR code, or  search the App store. 

OPEN iTAK    
& CREATE    
CALLSIGN 

Open iTAK and select “Get Started.”  Create your callsign. Using the nam ing convention provided, create your  callsign and add the phone number  associated with your device.  

Callsigns should be clear and con cise to avoid map clutter and proper ly identify your dot.  

Including your phone number en ables users from other channels (with  permissions) to call you without ever  sharing the information prior. This  can be extremely valuable in mutual  aid operations. 

Select next.   
![][image2]![][image3]SUGGESTED CALLSIGN CONVENTION \[Agency Acronym\] \[Last Name\] \[Radio Callsign\] *ex: DFPC Smith CH-32* 

• For common last names, a first name initial can be used \-  *CSP J. Smith 1A-08* 

• Your COTAK agency acronym may be viewed at cotak.gov under  your profile settings. 

• Agencies that operate outside of Colorado such as wildland fire fighters may add a two letter state abbreviation to the beginning of  the user’s callsign \- *CO ERFX Smith BC-2*

TEAMS (Colors) Tap the box titled, “Select Team.”  

Follow the convention provided for  selecting your dot color that will be  displayed in TAK. 

For special circumstances, users may  need to deviate from this convention.  Users are encouraged to use “open”  colors for temporary and special  

applications. 

Select your color then tap the box  titled, “Select Role.” 

ROLES 

Roles in TAK were intended for  military users, therefore not all first  responder roles are adequately  captured. 

When in doubt, users should default  to using the standard Team Member role. 

Once you’ve selected a team and  role, select next.

NOTIFICATIONS  & LOCATIONS 

Allow iTAK to send you notifications.  We will cover how to manage notifi cations in a moment. 

Enable iTAK to use location services.  Your apple device will populate a  prompt to allow iTAK to use your lo cation. You must select “Allow While  Using App” Your device may peri odically ask if you want iTAK to use  your location all of the time, or only  when using the app. You must select  “Always Allow.” 

Once both sliders are green, select  “Start iTAK.” 

NOTIFICATION  SETTINGS 

You will be sent to the main map  screen. 

Select the gear wheel in the upper  right hand corner of your screen. Se lect notifications, then the gray gear  wheel in the top right. 

We recommend utilizing the settings  provided on the right to avoid need less alerts. Adjust to your preferenc es 

for further assistance visit:  
Division of Fire Prevention & Control cotak.gov/support   
Center of Excellence for Advanced    
Technology Aerial Firefighting   
BASE MAP 

Return to the main map screen. Se lect the gear wheel in the top right.  Tap on “map source” you should  see “Apple” highlighted in front of a  map. 

Here you can select your preferred  map type. Most users will prefer the  Hybrid option. 

Return to the main settings menu. 

CONNECTING  TO COTAK  

Tap “Network,” then “Servers.” Se lect the plus arrow (+) in the bottom  right. Finally, tap on Scan QR. Scan  the QR code provided to the right. 

You will be prompted to enter your  username (full email) and password.  This connects you to your agency  and allows you to see other users. 

Return to the main settings menu. 

LAYERS 

Select “Layers” in the main settings  menu. 

Scroll to the bottom to toggle layer  settings. We recommend using the  configuration provided. 

Finally, to quit iTAK, swipe up to  display the app switcher and swipe  up on the iTAK application. Closing  iTAK will stop the sharing of your  location.
